Trend Analysis: How have total animal intake and euthanasia rates changed annually from 2004 to 2023, and what factors correlate with these trends?

In[13]:
import pandas as pd  
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt  

df = pd.read_csv('Animal_Care_and_Control_Division_Annual_Statistics.csv')  

# Line chart  
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))  
plt.plot(df['Year'], df['Total Intake of Animals'], marker='o', label='Total Intake')  
plt.plot(df['Year'], df['Euthanized'], marker='s', label='Euthanized')  
plt.title('Annual Trends: Total Intake vs. Euthanasia (20042023)')  
plt.xlabel('Year')  
plt.ylabel('Count')  
plt.grid(True)  
plt.legend() 
plt.savefig("'Annual Trends: Total Intake vs. Euthanasia (20042023).png")
plt.show()

Policy Impact: Did the introduction of "Impounds by ACO" in 2015 significantly alter the distribution of intake sources (strays, surrenders, impounds) or euthanasia rates?

In[20]:
# Grouped bar chart (pre- vs. post-2015)
df_pre = df[df['Year'] < 2015]
df_post = df[df['Year'] >= 2015]

# Use the correct column name from the dataset
intake_sources = ['Owner Surrenders', 'Strays', 'Impounds by ACO (Added in 2015)']
pre_avg = df_pre[['Owner Surrenders', 'Strays']].mean().tolist() + [0]  # 0 for missing pre-2015 data
post_avg = df_post[intake_sources].mean().tolist()  # Now includes the correct column

# Visualization
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.bar([x-0.2 for x in range(3)], pre_avg, width=0.4, label='Pre-2015')
plt.bar([x+0.2 for x in range(3)], post_avg, width=0.4, label='Post-2015')
plt.xticks(range(3), ['Owner Surrenders', 'Strays', 'Impounds by ACO'])  # Simplified labels
plt.title('Average Annual Intake Sources: Pre- vs. Post-2015')
plt.ylabel('Average Count')
plt.legend()
plt.savefig("Average Annual Intake Sources: Pre- vs. Post-2015.png")
plt.show()

fig.legend(loc='upper left')

Foster Program Impact: How has the growth in fostered animals influenced live release rates (adoptions + returns + transports + fosters) since 2005?

In[32]:
# Calculate live release rate  
df['Live Release'] = df['Adoptions'] + df['Return to Owner'] + df['Transported to other shelters and rescues'] + df['Fostered Animals']  
df['Live Release Rate'] = (df['Live Release'] / df['Total Intake of Animals']) * 100  

# Line chart  
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))  
plt.plot(df['Year'], df['Live Release Rate'], marker='o', color='purple', label='Live Release Rate')  
plt.plot(df['Year'], df['Fostered Animals'], marker='s', color='orange', label='Fostered Animals')  
plt.title('Live Release Rate and Fostered Animals (20052023)')  
plt.ylabel('Percentage/Count')  
plt.legend()  
plt.grid(True)
plt.savefig("Live Release Rate and Fostered Animals.png")
plt.show()

Operational Costs: What is the cost per animal intake (annual budget total intake), and how has this metric evolved alongside changes in adoption revenue?

In[38]:
# Calculate cost per intake  
df['Cost per Intake'] = df['Annual Budget'] / df['Total Intake of Animals']  

# Dual-axis line chart  
fig, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))  
ax1.plot(df['Year'], df['Cost per Intake'], color='blue', marker='o', label='Cost per Intake')  
ax1.set_ylabel('Cost per Intake ($)', color='blue')  
ax2 = ax1.twinx()  
ax2.plot(df['Year'], df['Annual Adoption Revenue'], color='red', marker='s', label='Adoption Revenue')  
ax2.set_ylabel('Adoption Revenue ($)', color='red')  
plt.title('Cost per Intake vs. Adoption Revenue (20042023)')  
fig.legend(loc='upper left') 
plt.savefig("Cost per Intake vs. Adoption Revenue.png")
plt.show()

Live Release Strategies: Which strategyadoptions, transports, or fosteringhas been most cost-effective in reducing euthanasia since 2015?

In[58]:
# Calculate cost per outcome  
cost_transport = df['Annual Budget'].sum() / df['Transported to other shelters and rescues'].sum()  
cost_adoption = df['Annual Budget'].sum() / df['Adoptions'].sum()  
cost_foster = df['Annual Budget'].sum() / df['Fostered Animals'].sum()  

# Bar chart  
strategies = ['Transports', 'Adoptions', 'Fosters']  
costs = [cost_transport, cost_adoption, cost_foster]  

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))  
plt.bar(strategies, costs, color=['#2ca02c', '#1f77b4', '#ff7f0e'])  
plt.title('Cost per Outcome by Strategy (20042023)')  
plt.ylabel('Cost per Animal ($)')  
plt.savefig("Cost per Outcome by Strategy.png")
plt.show()
